<title>CHILE: Bema sees expansion of Chile gold mine.</title>
<headline>Bema sees expansion of Chile gold mine.</headline>
<dateline>SANTIAGO 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bema Gold Corp expects to increase production at its Refugio gold mine in Chile to 500,000 ounces per year by 2000 from current design capacity of 230,000 ounces, said President Clive Johnson.</p>
<p>&quot;The mine has a potential of up to 500,000 ounces a year,&quot; Johnson told a news conference.</p>
<p>He said the expansion would cost between $75 million and $100 million.</p>
